node.text:
The safe landing brought a close to a two month mission that sent astronauts Bob Behnken and Doug Hurley to the International Space Station, as the final test of the Crew Dragon capsule that SpaceX and Nasa hope represent the future of spaceflight

Credit @nasa
.
.
.

node.text: The #Inspiration4 Orbital Sunset Nebula 🚀 What a launch!?! 🚀 not only for the visuals but for the purpose! This was a special one, four private citizens, who just a few months ago had no idea they would become astronauts orbiting the earth right now further away from our pale blue dot than any other human since the Apollo missions. Then, stack on top of it the mission has raised 131 million dollars and growing to fight childhood cancer by supporting @stjude and it’s truly out of this world exciting. Godspeed @inspiration4 crew! In this photo we see the second stage of the Falcon9 carrying the dragon capsule to orbit while the first stage starts to maneuver itself to land on the autonomous drone ship in the Atlantic Ocean all being lit up by the sunset IN SPACE. The orange glow is the sunset, and the transition to the blue glow is transitioning back to beginning of twilight all while on earth we’re observing the launch at @nasakennedy close to night… then, if that wasn’t enough to, complete with the Star field beyond the rocket away from the setting sun. Photo taken with a 10 year old @canonusa 1dx and a 400mm Canon lens, single exposure. Photo Credit: @erikkuna for @superclusterhq - #spacex #inspiration4 #rocketlaunch #spacexlaunch #spacexdragon #spacexfalcon9 #rocketsofinstagram #orbitaltwilight #rocketnebula #capecanaveral #nasa #elonmusk
